messages.content:
Sure! Here is an example of how the FinFit Advisor would call the `fetch_credit_score` tool:
```json
{
  "name": "fetch_credit_score",
  "arguments": {
    "user_id": "example_user_123",
    "consent_token": "<USER_OAUTH_CONSENT_TOKEN>"
  }
}
``` 
In a real request, the `<USER_OAUTH_CONSENT_TOKEN>` placeholder would be replaced with the OAuth token that the user has granted after a successful consent flow.
